New Records: The Dodgers became the first team in the majors to reach 80 wins with their victory over the Orioles
Key Match Events: The Dodgers manufactured four runs in the fourth inning on a bouncing, two-run double from Barnes, an RBI single from Mookie Betts, and a bloop single from Miguel Rojas. They added insurance in the eighth inning with a sacrifice fly by Tommy Edman.
Pre-Game Insights: The Dodgers held first baseman Freddie Freeman out of the starting lineup for a third straight game due to a fractured finger, expecting him to return soon. The batting order included several lineup changes, including Gavin Lux being dropped to the No. 8 spot.
Post-Match Reflections: Dodgers manager Dave Roberts expressed satisfaction with the team's performance and noted the importance of maintaining this level of play throughout the season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers' bullpen, which entered with the fourth-best ERA in August, played a crucial role in the victory, with Blake Treinen and Evan Phillips contributing key performances.
Others: The game was a crucial part of the Dodgers' push in the NL West, with the team looking ahead to a series against the Diamondbacks.
